/-!
# Brownian Markov property at the œÉ-algebra level

Degenne's `BrownianMotion` package proves the weak Markov property in the
function-valued form: `IsPreBrownianReal.indepFun_shift` states that the shifted
increment map `œâ ‚Ü¶ (X (t‚ÇÄ + t) œâ ‚àí X t‚ÇÄ œâ)_t` is independent (as a random
variable valued in `‚Ñù‚â•0 ‚Üí ‚Ñù`) of the past evaluation map
`œâ ‚Ü¶ (X t œâ)_{t ‚â§ t‚ÇÄ}`, and `IsPreBrownianReal.shift` states the shifted process
is again a pre-Brownian motion.

The textbook statement (Saporito, Theorem 5.1.4) is the œÉ-algebra form: the
post-`t‚ÇÄ` increment process is independent of the **natural filtration**
`ùìï·µâ_{t‚ÇÄ} = œÉ(X_u : u ‚â§ t‚ÇÄ)`. This file closes that gap: by
`Filtration.natural_eq_comap`, the natural œÉ-algebra at `t‚ÇÄ` *is* the comap of
the past evaluation map, so the function-valued independence upgrades to

  `Indep œÉ(shifted increments) (Filtration.natural X _ t‚ÇÄ) P`,

which together with `IsPreBrownianReal.shift` is the full textbook package: after
`t‚ÇÄ`, Brownian motion **restarts afresh, independently of its entire past**.

## Main results

* `shift_indep_natural` ‚Äî œÉ(increments after `t‚ÇÄ`) is independent of the
  natural filtration at `t‚ÇÄ`.
* `brownian_markov_property` ‚Äî the textbook package: the shifted increment
  process is a pre-Brownian motion *and* independent of `ùìï·µâ_{t‚ÇÄ}`.
-/

@[expose] public section

namespace MathFin

open MeasureTheory ProbabilityTheory
open scoped NNReal ENNReal

variable {Œ© : Type*} {mŒ© : MeasurableSpace Œ©} {P : Measure Œ©}
  {X : ‚Ñù‚â•0 ‚Üí Œ© ‚Üí ‚Ñù}

/-- **œÉ-algebra form of the weak Markov property.** The œÉ-algebra generated by
the shifted increment map `œâ ‚Ü¶ (X (t‚ÇÄ + t) œâ ‚àí X t‚ÇÄ œâ)_t` is independent of
the natural filtration `œÉ(X_u : u ‚â§ t‚ÇÄ)`. Upgrade of Degenne's
`IsPreBrownianReal.indepFun_shift` via `Filtration.natural_eq_comap`. -/
theorem shift_indep_natural (h : IsPreBrownianReal X P)
    (hX : ‚àÄ t, Measurable (X t)) (t‚ÇÄ : ‚Ñù‚â•0) :
    Indep
      (MeasurableSpace.comap (fun œâ (t : ‚Ñù‚â•0) ‚Ü¶ X (t‚ÇÄ + t) œâ - X t‚ÇÄ œâ) inferInstance)
      (Filtration.natural X (fun t ‚Ü¶ (hX t).stronglyMeasurable) t‚ÇÄ) P := by
  rw [Filtration.natural_eq_comap]
  exact (IndepFun_iff_Indep _ _ _).1 (h.indepFun_shift t‚ÇÄ)

/-- **Theorem 5.1.4 (Brownian Markov property).** For a pre-Brownian motion
`X` and any `t‚ÇÄ ‚â• 0`, the post-`t‚ÇÄ` increment process
`t ‚Ü¶ X (t‚ÇÄ + t) ‚àí X t‚ÇÄ` is itself a pre-Brownian motion, and it is
independent of the natural filtration `ùìï·µâ_{t‚ÇÄ} = œÉ(X_u : u ‚â§ t‚ÇÄ)` ‚Äî the
œÉ-algebra of the *entire* past, not merely finitely many past evaluations. -/
theorem brownian_markov_property (h : IsPreBrownianReal X P)
    (hX : ‚àÄ t, Measurable (X t)) (t‚ÇÄ : ‚Ñù‚â•0) :
    IsPreBrownianReal (fun t œâ ‚Ü¶ X (t‚ÇÄ + t) œâ - X t‚ÇÄ œâ) P ‚àß
    Indep
      (MeasurableSpace.comap (fun œâ (t : ‚Ñù‚â•0) ‚Ü¶ X (t‚ÇÄ + t) œâ - X t‚ÇÄ œâ) inferInstance)
      (Filtration.natural X (fun t ‚Ü¶ (hX t).stronglyMeasurable) t‚ÇÄ) P :=
  ‚ü®h.shift t‚ÇÄ, shift_indep_natural h hX t‚ÇÄ‚ü©

end MathFin
